0 sc0 ls0 ws0">monness makes its true spiritual meaning </div><div class="t m6e7 x1c he y1e65 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">obscure. Faith is more than belief. Belief </div><div class="t m906 x1c he y17c2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gives assent to testimony or doctrine. Faith </div><div class="t m406 x5a he y19c3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gives assent but unites trust and confidence </div><div class="t m43e x5a he y1b79 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to the belief and acts accordingly. Faith is </div><div class="t m6a3 x5a he y2115 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">thus an active principle, an act both of the </div><div class="t m143 x1c he y142 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">understanding and of the will, and unites </div><div class="t m9ff x5a he y1b86 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with it a response of the heart. In a special </div><div class="t m409 x5a he y217d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sense in this lesson faith is reliance on God&apos;s </div><div class="t m14a3 x33 he y236f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[ 28 I </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
